hopobject.body: Yes, I play the guitar varsperformancepills.net Some researchers have tried to plug the gap in data collection, including Gary Smith, of the Center for Injury Research and Policy at the Research Institute at Nationwide Children's Hospital in Columbus, Ohio. Smith has published studies documenting injuries from theme park rides, but has not published data about fatalities. In a paper published in May, Smith found an average of 4,423 injuries per year in amusement park riders under the age of 17.
